MMT done 700 m below GH WL trace after reset suggested that the gauge did not settle out after the purge.  This would result in an artifically high MGH. The MGH was computed by sampling the rate of stage change from 18:00 on May 17th to 18:00 on May 18th (0.069m in 12 hours). This rate of stage recession was then applied from the DWL on May 18th @ 11:15 until the mean time of the mmt @ 12:26. This results in a Corr MGH of 24.580m Sources:Manual
